It's time again for some pictures of this year's Wave Gotik Treffen. I've been looking forward to this since about December, and it was very great in the end, but much too short, and rather exhausting. Still, I won't complain too much.

I'm already pondering what outfits I will wear next year. I think the white one will make it into next year, and I want a complete golden outfit, and something fantasy-like, too. And perhaps a Geisha outfit. Anyway, a year is long and I still might not know what it'll bring in the end.

Ok, so this year I was at the WGT for the first time, and now pictures of me are popping up in every kind of german online newspaper... Oo here or here (pic 8) and various others, though with no different pictures than those... Kinda cool ^^

I'm surprised about it myself... but I've become hooked to the latest Starmania season ^^ I've read in my local paper that Nadine, a friend of me and my sisters made it into the show, and had to see that online. I know she wanted to enter the last two seasons already, but was too young then. Now she's 16 and according to may people, she's already the favourite. Mine too, of course... what a fucking awesome voice for this age. I hope she wins. Here's a video of her performance in the first show: Simon & Garfunkel - Bridge over Troubled Water Third Casting Second Casting First Casting Well, I've gotta watch every Friday evening now, even if I usually don't like casting shows...

This is just a short update to let you people know I'm still alive.
Now I'm home again for a change (though probably not for long) and I'm quite bored right now, I'll just have to make a senseless post. Usually when I'm with my hunter, I'm just too lazy or distracted... small wonder.
Anyway, I'll probably make another post tomorrow, because there are still some missing photos from almost three weeks ago, and sweet ones, too.

...which turned many tables and caused quite a few changes throughout the following week, and, as I just in this very minute got relayed, led to many a rumor deep in the Abyss, of which not all are false. So I promised to post pictures of my very own little realm a while ago, but haven't had any opportunity to actually do so until now. It is still not as perfect as I want, for there are things missing which I still have to earn more money for, but for the time being it shall suffice fair enough as refuge from everyday routine.
Bedside One. This bed I no longer use as bed, but plan to make it into some kind of couch. For this I still need to buy some cushions.

Aforementioned bedside at night.

This is my bookshelf and part of my altar of kitsch, for lack of better words.

Actually it is just a collection of pretty bits and pieces, and because this is mine, I set it alight.

The upper part.

Close-up of the lower part.

Close-up of the upper part.

The biggest dreamcatcher of currently five, dangling neatly from my pretty bluebell-and-ivy twine fairylights.

The real bedside this time. The rose chain covering the red fairylights is still missing in this picture.

Bedside at night, fairylights and star aflame.

Computer Side. The window still needs some kind of curtain.

Computer Side at night.

Pivoted upwards slightly.

This is the ceiling just above the bedside.

And this is the ceiling above the couchside.

This is the (unfinished) ceiling above the windowside.

And this is the same at night.
This is it so far, but as mentioned it's far from finished. I need cushions, curtains, a carpet and a small table plus drawers for starters, and more ivy vines to cover the walls would be nice too. Still, I probably should not dispense all my money for this at once. Still, pictures can never ever catch the true atmosphere as I experience it. They fail to catch the smell and sound at least. Anyways. It's probably much too colourful for many of you who might see it, but I live in there, 'nuff said.

Oh fuck I'm just cleaning up my room... I mean REALLY, I'm throwing away everything remotely unimportant and the things I found brought so many memories that I'm quite overwhelmed now. I found my drawings when I had just begun to draw, I found old chatlogs and the condolence cards from many people from when my mother had died, I found a love letter from Timothy (my first "relationship" that lasted about 2 weeks) that makes me feel even more uncomfortable for being this way then, I found lots of other letters and cards from online friends from very long ago, presents and letters from Caena, letters and sheets from Malachite, the world description from Norbert and so on... I suspect I haven't still found it all, but still.. I am quite shaken right now. This has reminded me much more of what I once was than all thinking before. Had I only needed it... Since I've found out of my personal mirror cabinet just before Christmas and more myself than since almost two years (since Dorian and a short time before, I suspect it was the Razor era), I wouldn't really have needed THAT many old memories now. *sigh* Well, at least my room'll be quite comfortable afterwards, because I have a creative flash right now, and I'm decorating it, but for that it's going to have to be clean and orderly.
